      <txt c="X" a="X" r="X" s="2" w="850" x="40" y="80" delay="0" pt="1" e="-3" align="left">The health authorities found out that the Captain declared the wrong expiration date for the medicine. The Captain wrote "1st June" instead of "1st July" of the next year. They ask the Captain for a few cartons of cigarettes, which the Captain gives to the health authorities.

How would the cigarettes be considered?</txt>
